org.openimaj.demos.sandbox.audio

Class AudioClassifier<ANNOTATION>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.openimaj.ml.annotation.AbstractAnnotator<SampleBuffer,ANNOTATION>
      • org.openimaj.demos.sandbox.audio.AudioClassifier<ANNOTATION>
  • Type Parameters:
    ANNOTATION - The annotation type
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Classifier<ANNOTATION,SampleBuffer>, Annotator<SampleBuffer,ANNOTATION>

    public class AudioClassifier<ANNOTATION>
extends AbstractAnnotator<SampleBuffer,ANNOTATION>
    A general audio classifier class that can use any annotator and any dataset. The AudioClassifier requires an annotator to be passed in, which in turn requires feature extractor. The feature extractor must be able to extract a FeatureVector from a SampleBuffer.

    The train(List) method takes a list of pairs, where the pairs are streams mapped to annotations. Each stream represents a set of SampleBuffers for that annotation. They are extracted into AnnotatedObjects before being passed into the annotator for feature extraction.
